:wrench: You can extract into parameter source. This would be cleaner. 

Something like the following:
```
 // Argument supplier
  static Stream<Function<TestCluster, TestStandaloneBroker>> restartTargets() {
    return Stream.of(
        ScaleUpPartitionsTest::restartBootstrapNode, ScaleUpPartitionsTest::restartBootstrapNode);
  }

  static TestStandaloneBroker restartBootstrapNode(final TestCluster cluster) {
    // if broker 0 is leader of partition 1, await until broker 0 is not leader of partition 1
    // restart broker 0
    return cluster.brokers().get(member0);
  }

  static TestStandaloneBroker restartPartitionOneLeader(final TestCluster cluster) {
    return cluster.leaderForPartition(1);
  }
```

Consider using a ByteArrayOutputStream instead of a List<Byte> for accumulating bytes. This may improve performance and simplify the conversion to a UTF-8 string.
```suggestion
            // Use ByteArrayOutputStream to accumulate UTF-8 bytes and convert to string line by line
            ByteArrayOutputStream lineBytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
```

